Things get even more complicated when Dan finds out that the woman he falls in love with is actually his brother's new girlfriend.
cast: Steve Carell, Juliette Binoche, Dane Cook, Alison Pill, Britt Robertson

title: Trenta Righe per un Delitto: Il Serial Killer dei Metronotte
description: A night watchman is killed and the newspaper La Provincia tries to build a scoop, pretending there is a serial killer behind it. However, someone tries to take advantage of it and within a short time the murders of other security guards follow one another. Walter, at odds with the editorial line, decides to investigate.
cast: Luca Barbareschi, Lucrezia Lante della Rovere, Toni Bertorelli, Sergio Fiorentini, Ramona Bădescu

title: Les Enfoirés 2016 - Au rendez-vous des Enfoirés
cast: Jean-Louis Aubert, Monica Bellucci, Bénabar, Patrick Bruel, Nicolas Canteloup

title: Tom and Jerry: Back to Oz
description: After capturing the good witch, the villainous King Gnome creates havoc throughout Oz as he needs Dorothy's ruby slippers to take control of the Emerald City. So, it is up to Tom and Jerry to save the land of Oz!
cast: Grey DeLisle, Joe Alaskey, Michael Gough, Rob Paulsen, Todd Stashwick

title: Never Sleep Again: The Elm Street Legacy
description: For decades, Freddy Krueger has slashed his way through the dreams of countless youngsters, scaring up over half a billion dollars at the box office across eight terrifying, spectacular films.
cast: Heather Langenkamp, Robert Englund, Wes Craven, Robert Shaye, Lisa Wilcox

title: Don't Let's Go to the Dogs Tonight
description: Growing up in the midst of the Zimbabwean War for independence, 8-year-old Bobo internalizes both sides of the struggle. Conflicted by her love for people on opposing sides, she tries to make sense of her life in a magical way.
cast: Lexi Venter, Embeth Davidtz, Zikhona Bali, Fumani Shilubana, Rob van Vuuren

title: The Claus Family 2
description: Jules Claus has embraced Christmas again and is getting ready for the busiest time of the year together with grandpa Noël. Everything seems to go according to plan, until Jules receives a very special letter with an intriguing question...
cast: Jan Decleir, Mo Bakker, Bracha van Doesburgh, Stefaan Degand, Eva van der Gucht

title: Romulus and Remus: The Story of Two Sons of a Wolf
description: The history of Rome revisited by the group of Bagaglino (Franco, Montesano, Castellacci and Pingitore). Romulus kills Remus, but also manages to get rid of him. The sister continues to bother him in the ghost robes. When Romulus founded Rome and abducted the Sabine, dies, hell, he is received, needless to say, the petulantissimo Remo.
cast: Enrico Montesano, Gabriella Ferri, Pippo Franco, Maurizio Arena, Maria Grazia Buccella

title: Object of Obsession
description: A divorced woman seeks new sexual adventures in this erotic tale. What she doesn't count on is that her new lover will take her as a hostage and hold her against her will.
cast: Scott Valentine, Erika Anderson, Elizabeth Whitcraft, Robert Keith, Jane A. Rogers

title: Uprostřed babího léta ve stepi zahoukal vlak
cast: Nina Divíšková, Jiří Dušek, Zuzana Fišárková, Jiří Bartoška, Karel Meister

title: Garage Sale Mystery: Murder Most Medieval
description: Jennifer finds the body of a local college history professor hidden in a suit of armor she purchased. After the professor's teaching assistant becomes the next victim, Jennifer finds herself caught in a killer's web of dangerous lies.
cast: Lori Loughlin, Sarah Strange, Steve Bacic, Eva Bourne, Connor Stanhope

title: Memoir of a Snail
description: Forcibly separated from her twin brother when they are orphaned, a melancholic misfit learns how to find confidence within herself amid the clutter of misfortunes and everyday life.
cast: Sarah Snook, Kodi Smit-McPhee, Jacki Weaver, Magda Szubanski, Dominique Pinon

title: El Macho in a Women's Prison
description: A man is locked up in a women's prison by mistake.
cast: Alberto Rojas, Rebeca Silva, Manuel 'Flaco' Ibáñez, Gabriela Goldsmith, Diana Ferreti

title: The Winter's Tale - Live at Shakespeare's Globe
description: The Winter’s Tale is Shakespeare’s great play of the irrational and inexplicable, illustrating how uncontrollable emotions can range across gender, country, class and age. Its universe is full of monsters, gods and natural disasters with a colossal sweep that takes audiences from the stifling atmosphere of the Sicilian court to the unbuttoned joy of a Bohemian festival. Staged at the beautiful and iconic Globe Theatre in London, this new production is directed by Blanche McIntyre and stars Will Keen (The Crown, Wolf Hall) as Leontes, Priyanga Burford (W1A, Marcella) as Hermione and Annette Badland (East Enders, Father Brown) as Old Shepherd.
cast: Will Keen, Priyanga Burford, Sirine Saba, Annette Badland, Oliver Ryan

title: The Boss Baby: Get That Baby!
description: Think you've got what it takes to be the boss? This interactive special puts your skills to the test and matches you up with one of 16 jobs at Baby Corp.
cast: Flula Borg, Alex Cazares, Rhys Darby, Pierce Gagnon, Jake Green

title: No Way to Treat a Lady
description: Christopher Gill is a psychotic killer who uses various disguises to trick and strangle his victims. Moe Brummel is a single and harassed New York City police detective who starts to get phone calls from the strangler and builds a strange alliance as a result. Kate Palmer is a swinging, hip tour guide who witnesses the strangler leaving her dead neighbor's apartment and sets her sights on the detective. Moe's live-in mother wishes her son would be a successful Jewish doctor like his big brother.
cast: Rod Steiger, Lee Remick, George Segal, Eileen Heckart, Murray Hamilton

title: The School of the Magical Animals
description: Ida Kronenberg must transfer to a new school, where she soon realizes the students are unkind to each other. However, that all changes when a new teacher, Miss Cornfield, begins to educate them on the value of friendship and magic.
cast: Emilia Maier, Leonard Artur Conrads, Loris Sichrovsky, Nadja Uhl, Justus von Dohnányi

title: Like Water for Chocolate
description: Tita is passionately in love with Pedro, but her controlling mother forbids her from marrying him. When Pedro marries her sister, Tita throws herself into her cooking and discovers she can transfer her emotions through the food she prepares, infecting all who eat it with her intense heartbreak.
cast: Lumi Cavazos, Marco Leonardi, Regina Torné, Mario Iván Martínez, Ada Carrasco

title: Open Your Eyes
description: Handsome 25-year-old Cesar had it all -- a successful career, expensive cars, a swank bachelor's pad, and an endless string of beautiful and willing women -- until he is thrown into a strange psychological mystery after a car accident scars his face and lands him in prison.
cast: Eduardo Noriega, Penélope Cruz, Chete Lera, Fele Martínez, Najwa Nimri

title: Simple Minds & a-ha in Concert: Engers Castle in Neuwied, Germany
description: a-ha and Simple Minds in Concert
cast: Morten Harket, Magne Furuholmen, Paul Waaktaar-Savoy, Jim Kerr, Charlie Burchill

title: Hunting Jessica Brok
description: Long before she was a single mother in a sleepy South African town, Jessica Brok was a highly skilled, coldblooded, special ops assassin. She thought she’d left that life behind. She thought her last ill-fated mission was her last. She thought wrong.
cast: Danica Jones, Clyde Berning, Richard Lukunku, Anthony Oseyemi, Hlubi Mboya

title: The Mafia Triangle
description: A Neapolitan camorra boss has retired from business but when his wife gets killed he gets back into action, and goes to the States to get his revenge.
cast: Mario Merola, Howard Ross, Lucio Montanaro, Massimo Mollica, Liana Trouché

title: K.G.F: Chapter 2
description: The blood-soaked land of Kolar Gold Fields (KGF) has a new overlord now - Rocky, whose name strikes fear in the heart of his foes. His allies look up to Rocky as their Savior, the government sees him as a threat to law and order; enemies are clamoring for revenge and conspiring for his downfall. Bloodier battles and darker days await as Rocky continues on his quest for unchallenged supremacy.
cast: Yash, Sanjay Dutt, Raveena Tandon, Srinidhi Shetty, Archana Jois

title: Return to Mayberry
description: After being away for awhile, Andy Taylor returns home to Mayberry to visit Opie, now an expectant father. While there he ends up helping Barney Fife mount a campaign for sheriff.
cast: Andy Griffith, Ron Howard, Don Knotts, Jim Nabors, Hal Smith

title: Alone in the Dark
description: Edward Carnby is a private investigator specializing in unexplainable supernatural phenomena. His cases delve into the dark corners of the world, searching for truth in the occult remnants of ancient civilizations. Now, the greatest mystery of his past is about to become the most dangerous case he has ever faced.
cast: Christian Slater, Tara Reid, Stephen Dorff, Will Sanderson, Ona Grauer

title: Abducted by My Teacher: The Elizabeth Thomas Story
description: The story of Elizabeth Thomas, a 15-year-old high school student who was groomed and abducted by teacher Tad Cummins.
cast: Michael Fishman, Summer H. Howell, Averie Peters, Adam Hurtig, Lisa Marie DiGiacinto

title: First Blood
description: When former Green Beret John Rambo is harassed by local law enforcement and arrested for vagrancy, he is forced to flee into the mountains and wage an escalating one-man war against his pursuers.
cast: Sylvester Stallone, Richard Crenna, Brian Dennehy, Bill McKinney, Jack Starrett

title: Tudo Por Amor ao Cinema
description: A documentary on Cosme Alves Netto (1937-1996), former head of the Cinematheque of the Museum of Modern Arts at Rio de Janeiro.
cast: Cosme Alves Netto, Carlos Diegues, Eduardo Coutinho, Nelson Pereira dos Santos, Fernanda Montenegro

title: Charlie Chaplin: A Tramp's Life
description: A biographical documentary about the great British actor and director Charlie Chaplin (1889-1977), from rags to riches, from the slums of London to glory.
cast: Peter Graves, Alec Hirschfeld, Andrew Sarris, Claire Bloom, Miloš Forman

title: Amaran
description: A heroic true story of Major Mukund Varadarajan, an Indian Army officer who displayed extraordinary bravery during a counterterrorism mission in Kashmir’s Shopian district. The film captures his courage in protecting his nation and the devotion of his wife Indhu Rebecaa Varghese.
cast: Sivakarthikeyan, Sai Pallavi, Rahul Bose, Bhuvan Arora, Lallu Prasath

title: Andrea
description: Andrea is a young woman with innocent looks, but a ravishing sexual appetite. By using her sexuality she can get most anything she wants, but as each days passes she gets deeper and deeper into a world that she despises and fears she will never escape.
cast: Dagmar Lassander, Gita Rena, Anne Famos, Ingrid Simon, Ralph Clemente

title: Surviving Compton: Dre, Suge and Michel'le
description: Discovered at a young age, the shy, squeaky-voiced Michel'le was plucked straight from South Central, Los Angeles and catapulted into the spotlight while riding N.W.A.'s rocket ride of early success. Surrounded by industry visionaries from Eazy-E to Tupac Skaur, Michel'le quickly climbed the charts, but her musical successes were soon overshadowed by betrayal and corruption. A nearly decade-long romance with the infamous Dr. Dre pushed her into a life tarnished by alcohol, drugs and violence until her savior came in the unlikely form of Suge Knight, co-founder of Death Row Records and Dre's business partner. Friendship would turn into a courtly romance, but the union Michel'le thought they had did not end happily ever after. With children from both men and a career to protect, Michel'le's voice became silenced by Compton's biggest power players. Until now.
cast: Michel'le, Rhyon Nicole Brown, Curtis Hamilton, R. Marcos Taylor, Jamie Kennedy

title: In the Line of Duty: Blaze of Glory
description: Former marine and cop Jeff Erickson starts a new life after meeting his dream girl, Jill, running a bookshop, until they decide to become the modern Bonnie and Clyde. Learning on the job the hard way, Jeff becomes famous through media-coverage, despite his power-trip tendency to bully his victims which becomes worse when Jill is hospitalized. FBI agent Tom LaSalle, has a hard time eliminating suspects and following the trail through
cast: Lori Loughlin, Bruce Campbell, Brad Sullivan, Susanna Thompson, Mariangela Pino

title: Circus in the Circus
description: To Moscow have arrived the participants of the international conference of the zoophilologists and also the international jury which is to elect for the world festival the best performance of the program of Moscow circus. Mrs Whistler (Iva Janzurová), British associate professor, makes her understood with the animals in their language but the Czech professor Ruzicka (Jirí Sovák), though he is capable of using the animals language, prefers teaching the animals the human language. Ruzicka's friend, the poodle Archibald, speaks "in Human" very well. The scientific dispute ends with a bet - if Ruzicka teaches the circus elephant to sing, Mrs Whistler will eat up her hat.
cast: Evgeni Leonov, Jiří Sovák, Iva Janžurová, Aleksandr Lenkov, Natalya Varley

title: Dance of the Drunk Mantis
description: A year after training young Jackie Chan in the Drunken Fist, Sam the Seed discovers he has a son, Foggy. He tries to train Foggy but to no avail. Foggy is then trained in Drunken Fist from his uncle as he must face his father's rival, Rubber Legs, another Drunken Fist master who combines it with Mantis Fist to create a deadly style.
cast: Simon Yuen Siu-Tien, Yuen Shun-Yi, Hwang Jang-Lee, Corey Yuen, Linda Lin Ying

title: Les Enfoirés 2021 - Les Enfoirés à côté de vous
description: Les Enfoirés "À côté de toi" is the 31st album/show by Les Enfoirés, recorded from January 14 to 17, 20211 at Lyon's Halle Tony-Garnier.  The show was recorded without an audience due to the Covid-19 pandemic.
cast: Ary Abittan, Kev Adams, Amir, Julien Arruti, Jean-Louis Aubert

title: Making The Flash: Worlds Collide
cast: Andy Muschietti, Barbara Muschietti, Jeremy Irons, Ezra Miller, Eunice Huthart

title: Paper Man
description: A coming-of-middle-age comedy that chronicles the unlikely friendship between failed author Richard Dunne and a Long Island teen who teaches him a thing or two about growing up, all under the disapproving eye of his long-suffering wife and his imaginary Superhero friend.
cast: Jeff Daniels, Emma Stone, Ryan Reynolds, Lisa Kudrow, Kieran Culkin

title: Yang Patah Tumbuh, Yang Hilang Berganti
description: Yasmin's happiness in managing a small inn in Solo with Darto disappeared after the arrival of Hardiman, Yasmin's father, who was a former legendary dancer.
cast: Clara Bernadeth, Indro, Donny Damara, Endah Laras, Dwi Windarti

title: What Men Want
description: Magically able to hear what men are thinking, a sports agent uses her newfound ability to turn the tables on her overbearing male colleagues.
cast: Taraji P. Henson, Aldis Hodge, Josh Brener, Tracy Morgan, Shane Paul McGhie

title: The Heaven None Missed
description: Pras and Arini's love was destroyed in Arini's eyes when he chose to marry Meirose secretly. Their ideal marriage collapsed instantly.
cast: Fedi Nuril, Laudya Cynthia Bella, Raline Shah, Kemal Palevi, Tanta Ginting

title: Such is Life
description: After her husband leaves her for a younger woman, the helping of her caring, but cynical godmother, is not enough to prevent Julia from plotting her revenge.
cast: Arcelia Ramírez, Patricia Reyes Spíndola, Luis Felipe Tovar, Ernesto Yáñez, Alejandra Montoya

title: Livers of Darkness: Making "Dude Bro Party Massacre III"
description: A documentary on the making of Dude Bro Party Massacre III.
cast: Michael E. Peter, Joey Scoma, Ben Gigli, Paul Prado, Jon Worley

title: Halloween 5: The Revenge of Michael Myers
description: After lying in a coma for a year, Michael Myers awakens and stalks his way back to his small hometown in Illinois, intent on killing his niece, Jamie, who has been confined to a mental institution since his last attempt to slay her.
cast: Donald Pleasence, Danielle Harris, Ellie Cornell, Wendy Foxworth, Beau Starr

title: Buzz Lightyear of Star Command: The Adventure Begins
genres: Animation, Family, Comedy, Science Fiction, Adventure
description: Buzz Lightyear must battle Emperor Zurg with the help of three hopefuls who insist on being his partners.
cast: Tim Allen, Nicole Sullivan, Stephen Furst, Larry Miller, Adam Carolla

title: Verdi: Simon Boccanegra (Salzburg Festival)
description: Power struggles among rival families in 14th-century Genoa, a story of tragic love, a young girl gone missing… Verdi’s Simon Boccanegra combines the perfect ingredients for gripping dramatic opera with a strong political message. On the stage of the Salzburg Festival, this sharp critique of power set to music is brought to life by the voices of Luca Salsi, Marina Rebeka, René Pape, Charles Castronovo, and others, who join the exceptional Valery Gergiev for a captivating performance.
cast: Luca Salsi, Marina Rebeka, René Pape, Charles Castronovo, André Heyboer

title: All Roads Lead to Rome
description: Maggie is an uptight, single mother and college writing teacher from New York City. In an effort to reconnect with her troubled teen daughter Summer, she decides to embark on a journey to a Tuscan village where she frequented in her younger days. Upon arrival, Maggie runs into Luca a handsome former lover who is still a bachelor and lives with his eighty-year-old mother Carmen. Summer (missing her “bad boy” boyfriend in NYC) and Carmen (secretly planning a wedding against Luca’s wishes to MARCELINO, her one true love in Rome) impulsively steal Luca’s car and race off to Rome. Maggie and Luca quickly pursue allowing the two mismatched couples to spend some time together and develop a new understanding of each other.
cast: Sarah Jessica Parker, Paz Vega, Claudia Cardinale, Raoul Bova, Rosie Day

title: Maybe someday, another history of French rap
description: In the early 2000s, the landscape of French rap undergoes a transformation, opening up to new horizons. A look at the birth, evolution, and legacy of an original rap that left a mark with its boldness and the novelty of its sounds and themes.
cast: Olivier Cachin

title: John Carter
description: John Carter is a war-weary, former military captain who's inexplicably transported to the mysterious and exotic planet of Barsoom (Mars) and reluctantly becomes embroiled in an epic conflict. It's a world on the brink of collapse, and Carter rediscovers his humanity when he realizes the survival of Barsoom and its people rests in his hands.
cast: Taylor Kitsch, Lynn Collins, Samantha Morton, Mark Strong, Ciarán Hinds

title: Vivo o muerto: El expediente García
description: Amidst the uncertainty caused by the alleged suicide of former president Alan García, journalist Carmen Ríos initiates an intense search aiming to unravel the mystery surrounding the case and answer the pressing question still lingering in the minds of all of Peru: Is Alan García alive or dead?
cast: Stephanie Orúe, Sergio Galliani, Omar García, Katerina D'Onofrio, Tatiana Astengo

title: A Nightmare on Elm Street
description: Teenagers in a small town are dropping like flies, apparently in the grip of mass hysteria causing their suicides. A cop's daughter, Nancy Thompson, traces the cause to child molester Fred Krueger, who was burned alive by angry parents many years before. Krueger has now come back in the dreams of his killers' children, claiming their lives as his revenge. Nancy and her boyfriend, Glen, must devise a plan to lure the monster out of the realm of nightmares and into the real world...
cast: Heather Langenkamp, Robert Englund, John Saxon, Ronee Blakley, Johnny Depp

title: The Master of Disguise
description: After the patriarch of the Disguisey family is kidnapped by Devlin Bowman in an attempt to steal the most precious treasures from around the world, Italian waiter Pistachio Disguisey utilizes his supernatural ability to disguise himself in an attempt to stop him.
cast: Dana Carvey, Brent Spiner, Jennifer Esposito, Harold Gould, James Brolin

title: Murder Commited in a Sly and Cruel Manner and from Low Motives
description: An eminent Belgrade physician is found murdered. The investigation reveals dark side of his character - illegal abortions and abuse of his wife. The wife's lover becomes the prime suspect. The newspaper reporter, however, starts his own investigation. Besides being a crime story, this movie in quasi-documentary fashion presents alternative cultural scene of Belgrade in late sixties.
cast: Mihailo 'Miša' Janketić, Irena Prosen, Zoran Milosavljević, Petar Kralj, Dragoslav Ilić

title: Pipo en de p-p-Parelridder
description: Pipo takes a walk in a ruin and awakens a knight who has been sleeping there for 500 years. Pipo reunites the knight with his great love, who has been waiting for him all this time. Pipo manages to keep the lovers out of the hands of Dikke Deur, Snuf, and Snuitje, who have very different plans for them. Pipo takes them to the wizard Miriardo, who must send the Knight and his beloved back to the past. Because that is where their future lies.
cast: Joep Dorren, Mariska Van Kolck, Rudi Falkenhagen, Karin Bloemen

title: A Quiet Place Part II
description: Following the events at home, the Abbott family now face the terrors of the outside world. Forced to venture into the unknown, they realize that the creatures that hunt by sound are not the only threats that lurk beyond the sand path.
cast: Emily Blunt, John Krasinski, Millicent Simmonds, Noah Jupe, Cillian Murphy

title: Henry Aldrich's Little Secret
description: Teenager Henry Aldrich and his pal Dizzy decide to try and earn extra money by starting a babysitting service.
cast: Jimmy Lydon, Charles Smith, John Litel, Olive Blakeney, Joan Mortimer

title: Gli strumenti del potere. 1925/1926 la dittatura fascista
cast: Antonio Salines, Paolo Bonacelli, Giacomo Piperno, Maria Fiore, Pino Colizzi

title: Jay and Silent Bob Reboot
description: Jay and Silent Bob embark on a cross-country mission to stop Hollywood from rebooting a film based on their comic book characters Bluntman and Chronic.
cast: Jason Mewes, Kevin Smith, Harley Quinn Smith, Aparna Brielle, Shannon Elizabeth

title: C'è un uomo nudo in casa
cast: Biagio Izzo, Giorgio Carosi, Daria Botte, Irma Carolina Di Monte, Corinne Cléry

title: WWE Best of Raw 2024 Special
description: Raw plays host to in-ring classics, jaw-dropping confrontations and shocking twists in this best of 2024 recap.
cast: Ettore Ewen, John Cena, Kofi Sarkodie-Mensah, Austin Watson, Joe Anoa'i

title: Microcosmos
description: A documentary of insect life in meadows and ponds, using incredible close-ups, slow motion, and time-lapse photography. It includes bees collecting nectar, ladybugs eating mites, snails mating, spiders wrapping their catch, a scarab beetle relentlessly pushing its ball of dung uphill, endless lines of caterpillars, an underwater spider creating an air bubble to live in, and a mosquito hatching.
cast: Jacques Perrin

title: Class of Nuke 'Em High 2: Subhumanoid Meltdown
description: At the Tromaville Institute of Technology's nuclear plant, Prof. Holt has perfected "subhumanoids": living beings without emotions who perform menial tasks. When school reporter Roger Smith meets a beautiful subhumanoid named Victoria, they fall in love and he becomes determined to save her and the school from a giant mutant squirrel, Tromie.
cast: Brick Bronsky, Lisa Gaye, Leesa Rowland, Michael Kurtz, Scott Resnick

title: Kubinke, der Barbier, und die drei Dienstmädchen
cast: Werner Fuetterer, Käthe Haack, Hilde Maroff, Julius Falkenstein, Fritz Kampers

title: Alabama Jones and the Busty Crusade
description: Alabama Jones, Oklahoma Jones, and California Jones are three sexy adventurers who hunt ancient treasures for a museum curator. They manage to defeat the floating flaming skulls that had killed previous treasure hunters and take the idol of Punani. Their next assignment is to find a drunken tracker named "Jungle Bill" and convince him to lead them to the Golden Mango of Tantu. During their quest they encounter sexy jungle goddesses, gorillas, natives, a hunky jungle man, a giant scorpion, lost aviator Amelia Airhead, and others while pausing frequently to enjoy erotic delights.
cast: Angela Little, Nikki Nova, Cheyenne Silver, Aria Giovanni, Sunny Leone

title: Rocco and His Brothers
description: When a impoverished widow’s family moves to the big city, two of her five sons become romantic rivals with deadly results.
cast: Alain Delon, Renato Salvatori, Annie Girardot, Katina Paxinou, Alessandra Panaro

title: I Know That You Know That I Know
description: The investigations of a private eye shake up the almost broken marriage of a middle aged couple.
cast: Alberto Sordi, Monica Vitti, Isabella De Bernardi, Salvatore Iacono, Giuseppe Mannajuolo

title: Here Comes the Boom
description: A high school biology teacher moonlights as a mixed-martial arts fighter in an effort to raise money to save the school's music program.
cast: Kevin James, Salma Hayek Pinault, Henry Winkler, Greg Germann, Joe Rogan

title: Tears at the Edge of a Prayer Rug
description: In this heartfelt drama, a mother discovers that a son she thought died at birth is still alive.
cast: Titi Kamal, Fedi Nuril, Citra Kirana, Muhammad Faqih Alaydrus, Krisjiana Baharudin

title: The Face I Can't Forget
description: While being cared for by her loving husband and daughter after a car accident leaves her with total amnesia, Mia begins having flashbacks of a second daughter, one no one else believes exists.
cast: Rayisa Kondracki, Victoria Baldesarra, James Gilbert, Rosie Simon, Liam Green

title: The one with eyes the color of time
description: A man suffers trauma after the poisoning death of his wife, and starts feeling responsible.
cast: Mirtha Legrand, Carlos Thompson, Zoe Ducós, Ricardo Galache, Antonia Herrero

title: School of Magical Animals 4
description: Ida's friend Miriam visits the school for three months, but a secret threatens to tear them apart. Miriam is entrusted with the tarsier Fitzgeraldo, while Max, deeply in love, is given the owl Muriel. The film, which is enriched with precious archive footage from the Cineteca di Bologna, including rare audio recordings and film clips shot behind the scenes, sees for the first time the direct participation of the Leone family and has interviews both with Leone’s longtime collaborators and with icons of Hollywood who have been profoundly influenced by his work.

title: Tutta colpa della SIP
cast: Gianfranco Bullo, Ana Obregón, Elena Fabrizi, Patrizia Della Chiesa, Toni Bertorelli

title: Metamorphosis of the Chief of the Political Police
description: In this film the director's recurring concerns return: the divisions in the Chilean left, and its contradictions between what the director calls the "traditional" and the "revolutionary" left. The problem is exposed through the doubts and obsessions of a strange police chief who cannot establish the limits between critical behavior and militant responsibility.
cast: Patricia Guzmán, Marcelo Romo, Rafael Benavente, Arnaldo Berríos, Enrique Madiña

title: Eine wen iig, dr Dällebach Kari
description: Kari Tellenbach was born with a cleft palate. His mother takes care of him like a bird that has fallen out of the nest. As a young man Kari decides to become a barber and despite his handicap he wins the heart of Annemarie with his humour, charm and sensitivity. His happiness seems almost complete – but Annemarie’s middle class parents have already made other plans for their daughter.
cast: Nils Althaus, Carla Juri, Bruno Cathomas, Julika Jenkins, Fabienne Hadorn

title: Sorry, Baby
description: Agnes feels stuck. Unlike her best friend, Lydie, who’s moved to New York and is now expecting a baby, Agnes still lives in the New England house they once shared as graduate students, now working as a professor at her alma mater. A ‘bad thing’ happened to Agnes a few years ago and, since then, despite her best efforts, life hasn’t gotten back on track.
cast: Eva Victor, Naomi Ackie, Louis Cancelmi, Kelly McCormack, Lucas Hedges

title: The Art of Love
description: A married couple, he a failed intellectual, she completely unsatisfied, try to solve their marital crisis by throwing themselves into the arms of two lovers; he a young Swede, she with a handsome Greek man.
cast: Janet Ågren, Silvano Tranquilli, Erna Schürer, Norberto Botti, Paola Corazzi

title: Ainbo: Spirit of the Amazon
description: An epic journey of a young hero and her Spirit Guides, 'Dillo' a cute and humorous armadillo and "Vaca" a goofy oversized tapir, who embark on a quest to save their home in the spectacular Amazon Rainforest.
cast: Lola Raie, Alejandra Gollas, Thom Hoffman, Bernardo de Paula, Dino Andrade

title: The Remains of the Day
description: A rule-bound head butler's world of manners and decorum in the household he maintains is tested by the arrival of a housekeeper who falls in love with him in post-WWI Britain. The possibility of romance and his master's cultivation of ties with the Nazi cause challenge his carefully maintained veneer of servitude.
cast: Anthony Hopkins, Emma Thompson, James Fox, Christopher Reeve, Hugh Grant

title: All's Faire in Love
description: Two rival medieval families compete for power and love in the fairytale world of the Renaissance. Will is a student who was sent by his professor to work in the fairgrounds after missing a few classes. Here he meets the kind and charming Kate, who quit her job at the bank to work at the fair. This is where this modern-day love story begins, in Renaissance garb!
cast: Christina Ricci, Owen Benjamin, Ann-Margret, Matthew Lillard, Jason Ishmael Echols

title: The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas
description: When his family moves from their home in Berlin to a strange new house in Poland, young Bruno befriends Shmuel, a boy who lives on the other side of the fence where everyone seems to be wearing striped pajamas. Unaware of Shmuel's fate as a Jewish prisoner or the role his own Nazi father plays in his imprisonment, Bruno embarks on a dangerous journey inside the camp's walls.
cast: Asa Butterfield, Vera Farmiga, David Thewlis, Jack Scanlon, Amber Beattie

title: Tender Mercies
description: Alchoholic former country singer Mac Sledge makes friends with a young widow and her son. The friendship enables him to find inspiration to resume his career.
cast: Robert Duvall, Tess Harper, Betty Buckley, Wilford Brimley, Ellen Barkin

title: An Indian in War - Life and Work of António-Pedro Vasconcelos
description: A retrospective on the life and work of Portuguese director António-Pedro Vasconcelos.
cast: António-Pedro Vasconcelos, Mário Barroso, Paulo Branco, Paulo Trancoso, Rogério Samora

title: London 2012 Olympic Opening Ceremony: Isles of Wonder
description: The London 2012 Olympic Games Opening Ceremony took place at 9pm on 27 July 2012. Titled 'Isles of Wonder', the Ceremony welcomed the finest athletes from more than 200 nations for the start of the London 2012 Olympic Games, marking an historic third time the capital has hosted the world’s biggest and most important sporting event. The Opening Ceremony reflected the key themes and priorities of the London 2012 Games, based on sport, inspiration, youth and urban transformation. It was a Ceremony 'for everyone' and celebrated contributions the UK has made to the world through innovation and revolution, as well as the creativity and exuberance of British people.
cast: Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom, Mike Oldfield, Kenneth Branagh, J.K. Rowling, Paul McCartney

title: El padre de mis hijos
description: Eva isn't having the best time: her boyfriend dumped her overnight, for no apparent reason, and she's forced to move back in with her parents. She decides to have her first child, but she has no one to be with, and what begins as a worry turns into an obsession.
cast: Mora Recalde, Julián Lucero, Horacio Fontova, Javier Drolas, Paula Carruega

title: Toy Story 4
description: Woody has always been confident about his place in the world and that his priority is taking care of his kid, whether that's Andy or Bonnie. But when Bonnie adds a reluctant new toy called "Forky" to her room, a road trip adventure alongside old and new friends will show Woody how big the world can be for a toy.
cast: Tom Hanks, Tim Allen, Annie Potts, Tony Hale, Keegan-Michael Key

title: Kitty and the Great Big World
description: The young Kitty is drawn into the world of international politics by chance.
cast: Romy Schneider, Karlheinz Böhm, O.E. Hasse, Ernst Schröder, Paul Dahlke

title: How to Play the Seduction Game
description: Armand seduces one woman after the other. However, he is supposed to consolidate his family's finances by marrying Amelie, a bankers daughter.
cast: Gundolf Willer, Yvonne ten Hoff, Véronique Vendell, Rudolf Schündler, Ralf Wolter

title: Trolls Band Together
description: When Branch's brother, Floyd, is kidnapped for his musical talents by a pair of nefarious pop-star villains, Branch and Poppy embark on a harrowing and emotional journey to reunite the other brothers and rescue Floyd from a fate even worse than pop-culture obscurity.
cast: Anna Kendrick, Justin Timberlake, Camila Cabello, Eric André, Amy Schumer

title: Ein Hund kam in die Küche
description: The teacher Senta falls in love with the award-winning chef Stefan, who rents out his romantic winegrower's house in southern Styria to her during the summer holidays. She soon notices that a quirky gendarmerie inspector is keeping the property under surveillance. Senta finds out too late that the policeman thinks Stefan is a multiple woman murderer and that she is trapped like bait.
cast: Tobias Moretti, Andrea Eckert, Karl Merkatz, Nicole Marischka, Heinrich Schweiger

title: Fall of the Mohicans
description: As Alice and Cora Munro attempt to find their father, a British officer in the French and Indian War, they are set upon by French soldiers and their cohorts, Huron tribesmen led by the evil Magua. Fighting to rescue the women are Chingachgook and his son Uncas, the last of the Mohican tribe, and their white ally, the frontiersman Natty Bumppo, known as Hawkeye.
cast: Jack Taylor, Sara Lezana, Daniel Martín, José Manuel Martín, Luis Induni

title: Pinuccio Lovero - Sogno di una morte di mezza estate
cast: Pinuccio Lovero, Simone Mezzapesa, Don Ciccio Acquafredda

title: The Book of Eli
description: A post-apocalyptic tale, in which a lone man fights his way across America in order to protect a sacred book that holds the secrets to saving humankind.
cast: Denzel Washington, Gary Oldman, Mila Kunis, Ray Stevenson, Jennifer Beals

title: Break Up
description: Paolo has been reasonably happy for the past 10 years; he has a job at the university and has Sena as a lover all these years. When she suddenly decides to leave the relationship, it comes as a shock to him, and he desperately wants to know the reason.
cast: Ornella Muti, Tony Musante, Monica Guerritore, Mario Scaccia, Laura Trotter

title: Aliens Abducted My Parents and Now I Feel Kinda Left Out
description: Itsy is new in town and her life seems over until she meets her space-obsessed neighbor Calvin, who believes his parents were abducted by aliens. An aspiring journalist, Itsy decides to write an exposé on Calvin but ends up discovering much more.
cast: Emma Tremblay, Jacob Buster, Will Forte, Elizabeth Mitchell, Matt Biedel

title: Lesbian Schoolgirls and the Pleasure of Perverting
description: Aunt Mary is not happy with her recent marriage. Her husband always wants to go to bed, and she doesn’t like it. Her sister’s daughter comes with a girl to spend some days in the house. Mary learns how to love both men and women.
cast: Concha Valero, Andrea Albani, Jordi Batalla, Mirna Bel, James Garci

title: You Should Have Left
description: In an effort to repair their relationship, a couple books a vacation in the countryside for themselves and their daughter. What starts as a perfect retreat begins to fall apart as one loses their grip on reality, and a sinister force tries to tear them apart.
cast: Kevin Bacon, Amanda Seyfried, Avery Tiiu Essex, Colin Blumenau, Lowri Ann Richards

title: Pres. Roosevelt's Fourth of July Oration
description: The best and most characteristic picture of the President ever made. The camera is close by so that every feature shows out sharp and distinct. The President is first seen coming on the stand laughing and shaking hands with friends and being wildly cheered by everybody. Then comes the speech. The President is very enthusiastic and is shown at his best. All his well known mannerisms are very apparent. The picture ends with a view of the departure of the President with Mrs. Roosevelt in a carriage. Before the carriage starts the President is held up and interviewed by reporters.
cast: Theodore Roosevelt, Edith Roosevelt

title: The Sword of the Barbarians
description: A swordsman's wife is murdered by followers of the evil Goddess Rani. He vows vengeance upon the cult and journeys to the Ark of the Templars to get a magic crossbow that will help him accomplish his mission.
cast: Pietro Torrisi, Yvonne Fraschetti, Mario Novelli, Xiomara Rodríguez, Margareta Rance

title: Witness to Murder
description: The director of a school is surprised by a student when murdering someone. He must kill the only eyewitness too, but his only clue is a number 32 shoeprint.
cast: Ray Milland, Sylva Koscina, Ramiro Oliveros, Franco Giacobini, Charly Bravo

title: Twice: The Extraordinary Life of Tsutomu Yamaguchi
description: Tsutomu Yamaguchi is a hibakusha. A survivor of both atomic bomb blasts in 1945. First at Hiroshima, then again at Nagasaki. Now nearing 90, Yamaguchi finally speaks out. Breaking taboos of shame and sorrow, he responds to a call to fight for a world without nuclear weapons by telling his story, so that no one else will ever have to tell one like it again. Twice reconstructs Yamaguchi’s experiences in 1945 Japan, interviews him on the after-effects of exposure and documents the last five years of the late-blooming activist’s life.
cast: Stuart Varnam-Atkin, Tsutomu Yamaguchi

title: The Six Wives of Henry Lefay
description: A presumed-dead man's current wife and former wives squabble over his funeral arrangements.
cast: Elisha Cuthbert, Tim Allen, Jenna Elfman, Andie MacDowell, Lindsay Sloane

title: Les Enfoirés 2019 - Le Monde des Enfoirés
cast: Ary Abittan, Amir, Julien Arruti, Jean-Louis Aubert, Bénabar

title: The Brotherhood of Justice
genres: Thriller, Action, Drama, Crime, TV Movie
description: High-school students start a vigilante group in their neighbourhood but, as their power increases, they become more abusive and dangerous.
cast: Keanu Reeves, Kiefer Sutherland, Lori Loughlin, Joe Spano, Darren Dalton

title: All the Presidents' Wives
description: A look at the women who has served as First Ladies of the United States.
cast: Barbara Bush, George H. W. Bush, Laura Bush, George W. Bush, Jimmy Carter

title: LEGO Marvel Spider-Man: Vexed by Venom
description: Thanks to Green Goblin and Venom, tech theft is now at an all-time high. Can our Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man put an end to their mysterious villainous scheme before all of New York City is destroyed?
cast: Robbie Daymond, Ben Pronsky, Josh Keaton, Tara Strong, Jennifer Hale

title: Balahibong Pusa
description: A young woman begins to unravel her stepfather’s dangerous obsession, pulling her into a seductive web of secrets that pits her against her own mother and spirals into a tense battle of desire and betrayal in this remake of the 2001 cult classic.
cast: Margaret Diaz, Mark Anthony Fernandez, Christine Bermas, Itan Magnaye, Yda Manzano

title: American Sniper
description: U.S. Navy SEAL Chris Kyle takes his sole mission—protect his comrades—to heart and becomes one of the most lethal snipers in American history. His pinpoint accuracy not only saves countless lives but also makes him a prime target of insurgents. Despite grave danger and his struggle to be a good husband and father to his family back in the States, Kyle serves four tours of duty in Iraq. However, when he finally returns home, he finds that he cannot leave the war behind.
cast: Bradley Cooper, Sienna Miller, Kyle Gallner, Cole Konis, Ben Reed

title: Había una vez un marido
description: Due to confusion, Rafael is believed responsible for the death of Teresa. His wife Lilia and his brother looking for the real culprits.
cast: Lilia Michel, Rafael Baledón, Pedro Infante, María Victoria, Yolanda Montes 'Tongolele'

title: The House of Flowers: The Movie
description: The De La Mora siblings concoct a mischievous plan to break into their old family home to retrieve a hidden treasure of significant importance.
cast: Cecilia Suárez, Aislinn Derbez, Dario Yazbek Bernal, Juan Pablo Medina, Paco León

title: Chanoc and the Son of Santo vs. The Killer Vampires
description: Chanoc fights alongside Santo's son against the Killer Vampires.
cast: El Hijo del Santo, El Santo, Nelson Velázquez, Arturo Cobo, Rubi Re

title: If You Meet Sartana Pray for Your Death
description: After a stagecoach is robbed and the passengers murdered, a long and tangled series of surprise attacks and murderous double-crosses, leaves the coach's strongbox in the hands of the killer Lasky. It is up to the legendary hero Sartana to track down the missing money and determine just who is ultimately behind the grisly robberies and killings.
cast: Gianni Garko, Fernando Sancho, William Berger, Sydney Chaplin, Gianni Rizzo

title: The Metropolitan Opera: The Marriage of Figaro
description: Conductor Joana Mallwitz makes her Met debut leading an extraordinary cast in Mozart’s comic masterpiece. Bass-baritone Michael Sumuel stars as the clever valet Figaro, opposite soprano Olga Kulchynska as his betrothed, the wily maid Susanna. Baritone Joshua Hopkins is the skirt-chasing Count, with soprano Federica Lombardi as his anguished wife and mezzo-soprano Marianne Crebassa as the adolescent page Cherubino. This live cinema transmission is part of the Met’s award-winning Live in HD series, bringing opera to movie theaters across the globe.
cast: Michael Sumuel, Olga Kulchynska, Maurizio Muraro, Elizabeth Bishop, Sun-Ly Pierce

title: Motel of Death
description: Murders take place in and around a hotel. Debuted on Mexican TV.
cast: Helena Rojo, Salvador Sánchez, Edith González, Carlos Cardán, Héctor Ortega

title: Fall for Me
description: Lilli is suspicious of her sister's new fiance, but when an attractive stranger enters her life, she's suddenly distracted by the thralls of desire.
cast: Svenja Jung, Theo Trebs, Tijan Marei, Antje Traue, Thomas Kretschmann

title: Dumb and Dumber
description: Lloyd and Harry are two men whose stupidity is really indescribable. When Mary, a beautiful woman, loses an important suitcase with money before she leaves for Aspen, the two friends (who have found the suitcase) decide to return it to her. After some "adventures" they finally get to Aspen where, using the lost money they live it up and fight for Mary's heart.
cast: Jim Carrey, Jeff Daniels, Lauren Holly, Teri Garr, Charles Rocket

title: March on Rome
description: March on Rome (Italian: La marcia su Roma) is a 1962 comedy film by Dino Risi with Vittorio Gassman and Ugo Tognazzi, aimed at describing the March on Rome of Benito Mussolini's black shirts from the point of view of two newly recruited, naïve black shirts
cast: Vittorio Gassman, Ugo Tognazzi, Roger Hanin, Mario Brega, Angela Luce

title: Rabbit School: Guardians of the Golden Egg
description: Rabbit Max, a juvenile shoplifter, gets trapped in an old-fashioned school. With rabbit girl Emmy, he acquires Easter Rabbits' secret skills, battles a sneaky fox family and learns about friendship.
cast: Noah Levi, Friedrich von Thun, Senta Berger, Jenny Melina Witez, Max Boguth

title: The All New Adventures of Laurel & Hardy in For Love or Mummy
description: Laurel and Hardy are in Florida where they meet archeologist Henry Covington, whose daughter they try to protect from the wrath of a mummy.
cast: Bronson Pinchot, Gailard Sartain, F. Murray Abraham, Jonathan Pienaar, Philip Godawa

title: A Star Named Ayrton Senna
description: The Official Film of Brazil's greatest Formula One driver, Ayrton Senna, who's sudden death in the 1994 San Marino Grand Prix sent shock waves around the World. It cemented his reputation both within the sport, and his native Brazil, as a legend. The film looks at his life and career using archive footage and featuring revealing interviews with the man, as well as those who knew him well; friends, family and competitors. It also shows how the Ayrton Senna Foundation, set up in his honor, is working to help under privileged and street-bound children in his native Brazil using sport as an incentive to learn. Written by Oliver Warman.
cast: Ayrton Senna, Viviane Senna, Jean Alesi, Martin Brundle, Juan Manuel Fangio

title: Da Best in da West 2: Da Western Pulis Istori
description: Sgt. John Paul Quezada (Dolphy) gets Col. Macanto (Babalu) through a series of unfortunate events. Sgt. Quezada is then moved to the homicide department and is partnered to crazy, rash policeman Larry Lopez (Lito Lapid). Madness ensues.
cast: Dolphy, Lito Lapid, Agot Isidro, Giselle Toengi, Babalu

title: The Man Who Could Work Miracles
description: An ordinary man, while vigorously asserting the impossibility of miracles, suddenly discovers that he can perform them.
cast: Roland Young, Ralph Richardson, Edward Chapman, Ernest Thesiger, Joan Gardner

title: Inspector Sun and the Curse of the Black Widow
description: After being put on indefinite leave by his chief of police uncle, the highly intelligent and arrogant huntsman spider Inspector Sun boards a San Francisco bound seaplane. Joined by an intrepid young fan, Sun is pulled into a murder case where the turnout could affect both the insect and human worlds.
cast: Fernando Cabrera, Andrea Villaverde, Catherina Martínez, Ana Jiménez, Txema Moscoso

title: El fascista, doña Pura y el follón de la escultura
description: The consortium of the people approve a proposal from the Mayor; instruct Ramon, a ruined sculptor, an equestrian statue of Franco. Luis, one of the councilors, visit Ramon and proposes the commission, Ramon rejects for ideological grounds, but after thinking it accepts as there are no marble equestrian statues. When Ramon finally finished the statue, the whole consortium believes it is past time to inaugurate a statue of Franco. To satisfy Ramon approve the making of a new statue. This is dedicated to democracy.
cast: José Luis López Vázquez, José «Saza» Sazatornil, Ovidi Montllor, Nieves Navarro, José María Cañete

title: The Lord of the Rings: The Hunt for Gollum
description: A new film based on the novels.
cast: Andy Serkis, Elijah Wood, Ian McKellen

title: Un marito per il mese di aprile
cast: Vanna Vanni, Carlo Romano, Pina Renzi, Guglielmo Sinaz, Romolo Costa

title: Cholos la ley del barrio
description: All bets are off between warring factions, led by two men known simply as The Tank and The Pork, in this drama starring Agustin Bernal.
cast: Agustín Bernal, Eleazar García Jr., Jorge Almada, Jessica De Val, Sandra Salas

title: Mune: Guardian of the Moon
description: When a faun named Mune becomes the Guardian of the Moon, little did he had unprepared experience with the Moon and an accident that could put both the Moon and the Sun in danger, including a corrupt titan named Necross who wants the Sun for himself and placing the balance of night and day in great peril. Now with the help of a wax-child named Glim and the warrior, Sohone who also became the Sun Guardian, they go out on an exciting journey to get the Sun back and restore the Moon to their rightful place in the sky.
cast: Michaël Grégorio, Omar Sy, Izïa Higelin, Féodor Atkine, Éric Herson-Macarel

title: Tom and Jerry: Robin Hood and His Merry Mouse
description: Robin Hood steals from the rich and give to the poor, and needs the help of Tom and Jerry! Your favorite daring duo aims to beloved medieval tale in a new film is all for one and one for all!
cast: Jamie Bamber, Charles Shaughnessy, John Michael Higgins, Grey DeLisle, John DiMaggio

title: Lady Chatterley II
description: Agatha and Martha are lesbian lovers. However, Martha starts a love affair with Christian, an unemployed sailor.
cast: Brigitte Robert, Patricia Bouvier, Patrice Chéron

title: Bedtime Stories for Grownups
description: Peter brings his new girlfriend Anja up to C. von Ficker's (i.e. Fucker's) flat, but their tryst is repeatedly disturbed by various events in the building. To calm the jittery Anja, Peter relates a series of erotic stories to put her back in the mood.
cast: Ulrike Butz, Judith Fritsch, Eva Gross, Sonja Jeannine, Heidi Kappler

title: Like a Bird on a Wire
description: A pseudo variety show about the Aufbau-Era, the time of the German 'economic miracle'. Brigitte Mira recounts her four husbands through song and joke, on a series of artificial sets.
cast: Brigitte Mira, Evelyn Künneke, El Hedi ben Salem, Ingfried Hoffmann, Kurt Raab

title: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Guardians of the Galaxy - The Thanos Threat
description: The Guardians are on a mission to deliver the Build Stone to the Avengers before the Ravagers, Thanos and his underlings steal it from them.
cast: Trevor Devall, Jonathan Adams, Will Friedle, Jennifer Hale, Stan Lee

title: The Return of Tommy Tricker
description: Welcome to the world of stamps with Tommy Tricker and friends as they learn the magic of travelling through time and space for the mere price of the postage. Though of course, nothing is as easy as it seems as they soon learn when they try to rescue Charles Merriweather, a stamp traveller frozen in time since his last attempt at stamp- travelling, 65 years ago. But Charles turns out to be a girl, his sister Molly! And she is rapidly turning into an old woman. To find a cure, Tommy takes off in a race against the time that leads him and Molly to the exotic and magical South Pacific islands.
cast: Michael Stevens, Joshawa Mathers, Heather Goodsell, Paul Nicholls, Mireille Thibault

title: Plamen a dým aneb Tajné lásky a veřejné omyly poštovního úředníka V. V.
cast: Václav Antoš, Eduard Cupák, Jana Hlaváčová, Svatopluk Matyáš, Jiří Doseděl

title: The Voyeur
description: At a college in Rome, a professor, nicknamed "Dodo" is in a deep depression. His stunningly beautiful wife has just left him for another man. Dodo wants her back very badly and has erotic daydreams about her. A beautiful young student in his class asks him for a ride home and seduces the lucky man, but still he wonders about his wife and her lover.
cast: Katarina Vasilissa, Francesco Casale, Cristina Garavaglia, Raffaella Offidani, Antonio Salines

title: The Worst Christmas of My Life
description: Paolo needs to reach the castle of Alberto Caccia, where he was invited to spend Christmas with his family and Margherita, the ninth month of pregnancy. With them there will also be blessed, daughter of Alberto and childhood friend of Margherita, who was also pregnant. Among various mishaps and blunders, Paolo will combine another of his, coming to make everyone believe, because of a misunderstanding, that Alberto's died for his fault.
cast: Fabio De Luigi, Cristiana Capotondi, Antonio Catania, Anna Bonaiuto, Dino Abbrescia

title: Jean Moulin, une affaire française
description: Drama set in the Second World War, focused on Jean Moulin, hero, martyr and symbol of the French resistance and the patriotism during the dark years of Nazi occupation.
cast: Francis Huster, Maruschka Detmers, Hubert Saint-Macary, Mélanie Laurent, Bernard Fresson

title: Shake Hands with the Devil: The Journey of Roméo Dallaire
description: The story of Canadian Lt. Gen. Roméo Dallaire and his controversial command of the United Nations mission to Rwanda during the 1994 genocide. The documentary was inspired by the book Shake Hands with the Devil: The Failure of Humanity in Rwanda which was published in 2003.
cast: Roméo Dallaire, Paul Kagame, Gerry Caplan, Mike Enright, Bill Clinton

title: Let's See How Fast This Baby Will Go
description: Pregnant and in labour, a teenager decides the best way to get to the hospital is to buy a new car. Based on Gloria Harrison's true story.
cast: Liv Hewson, Tara Morice, Steve Maresca, Emma Monk, Ben Hamilton

title: Judge Horton and the Scottsboro Boys
description: In 1930s Alabama, nine young black men are accused of raping two white women. The judge in the case, unlike the rest of the town, comes to believe that the boys are innocent and, against all advice from his friends and family, sets them free, which turns the entire community against him.
cast: Arthur Hill, Lewis J. Stadlen, Ken Kercheval, Vera Miles, Ellen Barber

title: The Red Thread
description: Seven years after their first infatuated encounter, Abril and Manuel meet again. Despite the fact that they are both married, it is soon apparent that their attraction has only grown.
cast: Eugenia Suárez, Benjamín Vicuña, Hugo Silva, Guillermina Valdes, Manuel Bozal

title: Death Magazine: or How to Be a Flowerpot
description: A documentary about "Death" magazine, founded by "Screw" Magazine founder and publisher Al Goldstein, and its eventual failure.
cast: Al Goldstein

title: Hantu Kak Limah 2: Husin, Mon dan Jin Pakai Toncit
description: After the events of "Hantu Kak Limah Balik Rumah", Husin returns to his village in order to deal with his money problems - which he has none of! In the village, Husin reunites with the usual patrons of Pak Jabit's stall and everything seems to be as normal as it could be. However, what Husin doesn't realise is that there is a new breed of evil returning after more than a century of slumber to claim the village's long standing debt and Husin too of course!
cast: Awie, Usop Wilcha, Rashidi Ishak, Avaa Vanja, Zami Ismail

title: The Way Way Back
description: Shy 14-year-old Duncan goes on summer vacation with his mother, her overbearing boyfriend, and her boyfriend's daughter. Having a rough time fitting in, Duncan finds an unexpected friend in Owen, manager of the Water Wizz water park.
cast: Liam James, Steve Carell, Toni Collette, AnnaSophia Robb, Sam Rockwell

title: Star Trek: Section 31
description: Emperor Philippa Georgiou joins a secret division of Starfleet tasked with protecting the United Federation of Planets and faces the sins of her past.
cast: Michelle Yeoh, Omari Hardwick, Sam Richardson, Kacey Rohl, Sven Ruygrok

title: Up the MacGregors
description: Seven brothers team up to rescue their gold and their women from a ruthless bandit.
cast: David Bailey, Agata Flori, Alberto Dell'Acqua, Roberto Camardiel, Hugo Blanco

title: Juicio contra un ángel
description: A widower arrives in Puerto Rico with his son Angelito. The father dies and the boy goes to live with his grandfather who plays guitar in the streets. Angelito accompanies him singing and earns good money, but a political uncle accuses the grandfather of exploiting the boy and takes him to an orphanage.
cast: Angelito, Dacia González, Rafael Bertrand, Maribella García, Braulio Castillo

title: Sing
description: A koala named Buster recruits his best friend to help him drum up business for his theater by hosting a singing competition.
cast: Matthew McConaughey, Reese Witherspoon, Seth MacFarlane, Scarlett Johansson, John C. Reilly

title: Il bambino sull'acqua
cast: Giuseppe Fiorello, Vittoria Belvedere, Mattia d'Alesio, Valeria Fabrizi, Francesco Salvi

title: The Queen v Patrick O'Donnell
description: The Queen -v- Patrick O'Donnell reveals on screen for the first time the true story behind one of the most compelling murder plots in Irish history, a thrilling tale of violence, courtroom drama, romance and political intrigue. Containing evidence from British Home Office files kept secret for 100 years, it reveals shocking new information about the fate of the quiet-spoken Donegal man who killed the infamous informer James Carey on board a ship off the coast of South Africa in 1883. What possessed the illiterate labourer from the Donegal Gaeltacht to shoot the leader of The Invincibles? Who was the mystery woman posing as his wife? And why did both the US President and the French luminary Victor Hugo plead that Patrick O'Donnell not be hanged for his crime?
cast: Eoghan Mac Giolla Bhride, Stephen Jones, Bridin Ni Mhaoldomhnaigh, Sophie Campbell, Eoin Geoghegan

title: The Rule of Jenny Pen
description: Confined to a secluded rest home and trapped within his stroke-ridden body, a former Judge must stop an elderly psychopath who employs a child's puppet to abuse the home's residents with deadly consequences.
cast: Geoffrey Rush, John Lithgow, George Henare, Nikki MacDonnell, Maaka Pohatu

title: Wien, wie es weint und lacht
cast: John Mylong, Mady Christians, Hans Brausewetter, Hermann Picha, Julius Falkenstein

title: Big
description: When a young boy makes a wish at a carnival machine to be big—he wakes up the following morning to find that it has been granted and his body has grown older overnight. But he is still the same 13-year-old boy inside. Now he must learn how to cope with the unfamiliar world of grown-ups including getting a job and having his first romantic encounter with a woman.
cast: Tom Hanks, Elizabeth Perkins, Robert Loggia, John Heard, Jared Rushton

title: When a Stranger Calls Back
description: A retired detective and a crisis-center counselor hunt a killer stalking a coed.
cast: Carol Kane, Charles Durning, Jill Schoelen, Gene Lythgow, Karen Elizabeth Austin

title: The Muckles - The Quest for a New Home
description: Once upon a time, the Mucklas could be found everywhere. But in an increasingly tidy world, the cheerful goblins have a hard time, since they love disorder more than anything. Soon the last tribe will have to leave their home. For generations, the little creatures have made themselves at home unnoticed in Hansson's old, chaotic grocer's store. In the wonderful mess, they find everything they need to live, tinker and make mischief. But Hansson's successor, Karl the exterminator, turns the paradise into a tiled and sterile nightmare. So Svunja, Tjorben and Smartö set off on a dangerous search for the promised land. The great adventure begins
cast: Uwe Ochsenknecht, André Jung, Christine Urspruch, Marianne Sägebrecht, Stefan Kurt

title: El Carro de la Muerte
cast: Roberto 'El Flaco' Guzmán, Rosenda Bernal, Sergio Goyri, Víctor Alcocer, Luis Accinelli

title: The Latest Scams of El Torete
description: While the Torete rob banks, the Heifer, another delinquent who has not noticed it, enters the same place to rob him. After failing the coup, both decide to associate.
cast: Ángel Fernández Franco, Bernard Seray, Berta Cabré, Isabel Mestres, Fernando Guillén

title: Diana - Die Nacht, in der sie zur Legende wurde
cast: Mareile Blendl, Patrick Pinheiro, Dirk Ossig, Maximilian Dirr, Felix Hellmann

title: The Sweet Body of Deborah
description: A newlywed couple visits the husband's hometown of Geneva, where they are subjected to threats stemming from the death of his former fiancée.
cast: Carroll Baker, Jean Sorel, Ida Galli, Luigi Pistilli, Michel Bardinet

title: Napoli... i 5 della squadra speciale
description: In Naples, gangsters have seized the American ambassador. The authorities respond by assembling a special squad; to command it is Borri, a former commissioner who has a personal vendetta against the racket.
cast: Richard Harrison, Lina Polito, Enrico Maisto, Franco Marino, Tommaso Palladino

title: Bar 20 Rides Again
description: Cattle rustler Nevada dreams of living like an emperor in the West. Hoppy and the Bar 20 boys aim to put an end to his dream.
cast: William Boyd, James Ellison, Jean Rouverol, George 'Gabby' Hayes, Harry Worth

title: Ace Ventura: Pet Detective
description: He's Ace Ventura: Pet Detective. Jim Carrey is on the case to find the Miami Dolphins' missing mascot and quarterback Dan Marino. He goes eyeball to eyeball with a man-eating shark, stakes out the Miami Dolphins and woos and wows the ladies. Whether he's undercover, under fire or underwater, he always gets his man… or beast!
cast: Jim Carrey, Courteney Cox, Sean Young, Tone Loc, Dan Marino

title: The Dragon, The Odds
description: Mo is a gifted student in one of the village's dozens upon dozens of kung-fu schools. But when the master's away, he leaves the place in the hands of his best student Kang. But Kang rules with a cruel, iron fist. Little does anyone know, however, Kang is really the pupil of his Masters' old nemesis Ken Mo Fung 'The Golden Tiger'. Fung has instructed Kang to discredit the school publicly, then kill his Master by poisoning his tea.
cast: Yuen Bo, Alan Chan Kwok-Kuen, Sai Gwa-Pau, Lo Hoi-Pang, Kwan Hoi-San

title: Prometheus
description: A team of explorers discover a clue to the origins of mankind on Earth, leading them on a journey to the darkest corners of the universe. There, they must fight a terrifying battle to save the future of the human race.
cast: Noomi Rapace, Michael Fassbender, Charlize Theron, Idris Elba, Guy Pearce

title: The Year of the Plague
description: After the end of his relationship with Irene, friends and co-workers attempt to find Victor a new girlfriend, but even after he starts a relationship with Lola, he does not want to forget Irene. His existence is suddenly turned upside down when inexplicable things start to happen around him.  Something is possessing people, causing their behaviour to change.
cast: Ivan Massagué, Ana Serradilla, Miriam Giovanelli, Brays Efe, Sue Flack

title: Conrad & Michelle: If Words Could Kill
description: Two suicidal teenagers, Conrad and Michelle, turn to each other for support, communicating via text messages. But when Conrad expresses his desire to end his life, instead of trying to stop him as she had previously, Michelle encourages Conrad to take his life, even providing him suggestions on how to do it.
cast: Bella Thorne, Austin P. McKenzie, Paula Marshall, Rodney Rowland, Michelle Borth

title: Me, Myself and My Dead Wife
description: Bernardo is a renowned architect and professor at the University  of Buenos Aires. He just buried his wife, refusing to fulfill her desire to be cremated and her ashes scattered into “Costa del Sol”. Only when his wife’s grave  is desecrated, he decides to take the trip to Spain. With Abel, owner of a  bankrupt real estate business, and Amalia, a beautiful public relations  employee, Bernardo will be involved in absurd situations to get rid of the  ashes of his wife. Bernardo will discover that he didn’t know his wife as  much as he imagined.
cast: Oscar Martínez, Carlos Areces, Ingrid García Jonsson, Malena Solda, Cris Nollet

title: A Somewhat Gentle Man
description: After serving a 12-year sentence for killing the man that slept with his wife, a man ponders whether he should try and reconcile with his family, or take revenge on those who turned him in.
cast: Stellan Skarsgård, Jorunn Kjellsby, Bjørn Floberg, Gard B. Eidsvold, Jannike Kruse

title: Christmas with the Kranks
description: When their only daughter Blair leaves the family nest, Luther and Nora Krank decide to book an island cruise to beat the yuletide blues and just skip the holidays. But their decision to boycott tradition has the whole neighborhood in an uproar, and when Blair calls on Christmas Eve to announce a surprise visit with her new fiancée, the Kranks have just twelve hours to perform a miracle and pull themselves and their neighbors together to throw the best celebration ever!
cast: Tim Allen, Jamie Lee Curtis, Dan Aykroyd, M. Emmet Walsh, Elizabeth Franz

title: „Rakev ve snu viděti...“
description: The Ronov castle has been changed into a hotel, offering stylish facilities to its guests: weddings in the torture chamber, a Black Lancer kidnapping brides, a night's lodging in a family tomb etc. The reformed petty swindler Felix Pacínek (Bohumil Smída) runs the hotel. The business is far from thriving; the place is half-empty, and the jazz band Skeleton, together with their singer Zuzanka (Jaroslava Obermaierová), decide to leave. Nobody in the hotel has any idea that the band is in fact a gang of thieves who have just robbed the Prague State Bank, taking two million crowns from its vaults.
cast: Bohumil Šmída, Jaroslava Obermaierová, Zdeněk Dítě, Čestmír Řanda, Lubomír Kostelka

title: Fertile La Toyah Video Magazine #2: The Kinky Issue!
description: Prostrate probing interviews! Live action murder! Naked people! Tired death-rockers! And more! Much more!!
cast: Vaginal Davis, Fertile La Toyah Jackson, GG Allin, Karen Black, Flea

title: Which of These Two Ladies Is He Married To?
cast: Georgina Hale, Glenda Jackson, Patricia Lawrence, Sheila Raynor, William Squire

title: Adored
description: South of France: Riki Kandinski and his elder brother Fredrico, come back to their family castle for their father's funeral. Fredrico knows nothing about his younger brother, but he notices that he is making big money and living in luxury all for a few days work a week. By pure chance, Fredrico gets his hands on a gay porn magazine and sees his brother in it.
cast: Marco Filiberti, Urbano Barberini, Alessandra Acciai, Rosalinda Celentano, Francesca D'Aloja

title: The Sweet Sounds of Life
description: Sofia, a budding young theater actress, unwittingly discovers that Bruno, her beloved acting teacher, is gay. Heartbroken and determined to flee as far away from him as possible, she meets a young girl on the train who gives birth and abandons the baby. Sofia makes a life-changing decision: she takes the child and passes him off as her own son, naming him Bruno.
cast: Francesca Neri, Rade Šerbedžija, Claudio Biscione, Niccolò Senni, Rosalinda Celentano

title: The Road to El Camino: Behind the Scenes of El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie
description: Aaron Paul, Vince Gilligan and other cast members, producers and crew share stories and footage from the making of "El Camino."
cast: Aaron Paul, Charles Baker, Matt Jones, Jonathan Banks, Krysten Ritter

title: Saved By The Bell: Hawaiian Style
description: Kelly's grandpa invites the whole gang to his little hotel "The Hideaway" in Hawaii for summer vacation. They expect a marvelous time at the beach - without Belding. Upon arriving, they quickly learn that not only is Belding there, but they also have to help Kelly's grandpa from losing his hotel. Meanwhile Zack meets (again) the love of his life, Jessie and Slater bet with Lisa that they won't fight, and Screech gets kidnapped by the Pupuku clan.
cast: Mark-Paul Gosselaar, Tiffani-Amber Thiessen, Mario López, Dustin Diamond, Elizabeth Berkley

title: Joan the Maid I: The Battles
description: Convinced that only she can lead France to victory against the invading English, Jeanne d'Arc leaves her childhood home to plead Charles, heir to the French throne, to allow her to guide his troops on the battlefield.
cast: Sandrine Bonnaire, Tatiana Moukhine, Jean-Marie Richier, Baptiste Roussillon, Jean-Luc Petit

title: Forget Everything I've Told You
description: A tragic-comedy over a dysfunctional Portuguese family. The story of six people who love, hate, split up and meet again - Messias, the husband, a dentist, almost magician; Felizbela, the beautiful wife, almost happy; Joana, the daughter and her boyfriend, almost famous and the grandfather Tobias, a shepherd, almost imortal. Six characters, six stories, one film: Forget Everything I've Told You.
cast: Custódia Gallego, António Capelo, Cleia Almeida, Amélia Corôa, Fernando Taborda

title: Kerouac's Road: The Beat of a Nation
description: Jack Kerouac's "On the Road" finds new relevance as modern travelers and cultural figures like Josh Brolin, W. Kamau Bell and Natalie Merchant reveal how his quest for authentic experience resonates powerfully in our screen-saturated era — offering a lyrical meditation on what it means to truly experience the journey.
cast: Michael Imperioli, W. Kamau Bell, Josh Brolin, Matt Dillon, Natalie Merchant

title: How to Undress in Front of Your Husband
description: A "Peeping Tom" likes to look through windows at women undressing. We see him as he sneaks a peek at two subjects. The first, a woman dressed in lingerie, is young, shapely and attractive. The second, to be charitable, isn't. That doesn't stop him, and the viewer, from getting an eyeful.
cast: Elaine Barrie, Trixie Friganza, Hal Richardson, Albert Van Antwerp

title: John Mulaney: The Comeback Kid
description: Armed with boyish charm and a sharp wit, the former "SNL" writer offers sly takes on marriage, his beef with babies and the time he met Bill Clinton.
cast: John Mulaney, Amanda Walsh

title: Taipei Factory
description: A collaborative project consisting four young generation of Taiwan directors, and four young foreign directors from Chile, France, Iran, and South Korea.Without being acquainted previously before meeting each other in Taipei, the eight of them shared their life experiences, and then co-wrote and co-directed four short films based on impressions and imaginations of a city.
cast: Jack Kao

title: LEGO Star Wars: The Padawan Menace
description: Master Yoda must go retrieve secret battle plans. However, things become a little more complicated when a class of younglings join the mission.
cast: Anthony Daniels, Nika Futterman, Phil LaMarr, Tom Kane, Katie Leigh

title: Prisoner Trump: The Don of Cell Block B
description: When Donald Trump and Rudy Giuliani are sent to prison, Trump seizes the moment to build his next empire. Armed with “Trump Bucks” and outrageous plans, he seeks to rule the prison in this clever and biting political satire.
cast: Jim Storm, Patrick M.J. Finerty, Howard McNair, Alex Veadov, Jay Krymis

title: Marco Polo: One Hundred Eyes
description: A defiant warrior-monk arrives at Kublai Khan's court in chains and soon earns his tragic nickname in this 30-minute origin story.
cast: Tom Wu, Masayoshi Haneda, Benedict Wong, Michelle Yeoh

title: La ciudad no es para mí
description: Agustin, a widower who lives in a village in Aragon, where he is much loved by all neighbors, is lonely and decides to go to the big city, where his son, a famous doctor, lives with his wife and daughter. Agustineis received by his children with great coolness, as he does not fit in the environment in which they operate. The life of his son, his daughter-in-law, and even the maid is too sad for this simple town man.
cast: Paco Martínez Soria, Doris Coll, Eduardo Fajardo, Sancho Gracia, Alfredo Landa

title: Professionals for a Massacre
description: Caught selling stolen guns, three Confederate soldiers get a reprieve from the firing squad, provided they go into Mexico on a mission to recover stolen gold belonging to the Confederacy.
cast: George Hilton, Edd Byrnes, George Martin, Mónica Randall, Milo Quesada

title: Brother Bear 2
description: Kenai finds his childhood human friend Nita and the two embark on a journey to burn the amulet he gave to her before he was a bear, much to Koda's dismay.
cast: Patrick Dempsey, Mandy Moore, Jeremy Suarez, Rick Moranis, Dave Thomas

title: Du Schmilblick aux Restos du Cœur, la folle histoire de Coluche
cast: Coluche, Martin Lamotte, Maryse Gildas, Philippe Gildas, Michel Boujenah

title: Electra One
description: A jewel thief crosses paths with a woman carrying a briefcase that the Americans, the Russians and the Chinese all want desperately, so he goes on the run with her figuring that what's inside the case has to be way more valuable than anything he could steal on his own.
cast: George Martin, Vivi Bach, Klausjürgen Wussow, Daniele Vargas, Rosalba Neri

title: 2019: After the Fall of New York
description: After a nuclear war society breaks down into two groups, the evil Euraks, and the rebel Federation. A mercenary named Parsifal is hired by the Federation to infiltrate New York City, which is controlled by the Euraks, to rescue the only fertile woman left on Earth.
cast: Michael Sopkiw, Valentine Monnier, Anna Kanakis, George Eastman, Romano Puppo

title: Iran: The Hundred Year War
description: What kind of world power is Iran becoming, and how will Western countries deal with it?
cast: Abbas Abdi, Mahmoud Ahmadinejad, Osama bin Laden, Zbigniew Brzezinski, George W. Bush

title: Dead Men Don't Make Shadows
description: Lazar, a bounty killer, teams up with a young gunfighter to blackmail Barrett, a former bandit and mine owner. At the end of the day, the bounty hunter clashes with Barrett, but something goes wrong.
cast: Jack Betts, Franco Borelli, Gordon Mitchell, Simonetta Vitelli, Benito Pacifico

title: Celebração - 100 Anos do Cinema Nacional
description: "Portraits and excerpts from Brazilian films from all times. Actors, directors and images that affirm cinema."
cast: Adelaide Chiozzo, Adriana Prieto, Aida Leiner, Alberto Ruschel, Alda Garrido

title: Lotte Jäger und das tote Mädchen
cast: Silke Bodenbender, Sebastian Hülk, Anna Maria Mühe, Isolda Dychauk-Ott, Andreas Schmidt-Schaller

title: Jack and the Cuckoo-Clock Heart
description: Jack is born with his heart frozen solid on the coldest day in history. A wise midwife saves him by replacing it with a cuckoo clock. Now Jack must abide by three rules to keep his mechanical heart safe: never touch the clock's hands, master his anger, and never fall in love. He tries his best, but when he meets a girl named Acacia he falls in love, threatening the delicate balance of his artificial heart.
cast: Mathias Malzieu, Olivia Ruiz, Grand Corps Malade, Jean Rochefort, Emily Loizeau

title: Land of Bad
description: When a Delta Force special ops mission goes terribly wrong, Air Force drone pilot Reaper has 48 hours to remedy what has devolved into a wild rescue operation. With no weapons and no communication other than the drone above, the ground mission suddenly becomes a full-scale battle when the team is discovered by the enemy.
cast: Liam Hemsworth, Russell Crowe, Luke Hemsworth, Ricky Whittle, Milo Ventimiglia

title: The Wild Chicks and Life
description: The Wild Chicks are slowly growing out of their youthful gang years and have to face the worries of growing up on the sidelines of a big class trip before graduation.
cast: Michelle von Treuberg, Lucie Hollmann, Sonja Gerhardt, Jette Hering, Zsá Zsá Inci Bürkle

title: Lady of the Camelias
description: A young girl from the provinces, comes to Paris with one goal: to become a part of the rich bourgeoisie. To achieve this she will use her unique beauty and charm.
cast: Isabelle Huppert, Gian Maria Volonté, Bruno Ganz, Fabrizio Bentivoglio, Clio Goldsmith

title: 127 millones libres de impuestos
cast: José Luis López Vázquez, Amparo Soler Leal, Amparo Baró, Agustín González, Carlos Larrañaga

title: The First Day of My Life
description: In the exact moment they hit rock bottom, four strangers are visited by a mysterious man who gifts them a week to see how the world would be without them.
cast: Toni Servillo, Margherita Buy, Valerio Mastandrea, Sara Serraiocco, Gabriele Cristini

title: The Death of the Duke of Enghien in 1804
description: Directed by Albert Capellani.
cast: Paul Capellani, Nelly Cormon, René Leprince, Daniel Mendaille, Henri Étiévant

title: Lo'Waist Gang at si Og sa Mindoro
cast: Fernando Poe Jr., Jess Ramos, Teresita Mendez, Berting Labra, Boy Francisco

title: Justice League x RWBY: Super Heroes & Huntsmen, Part Two
description: On the heels of successfully escaping a deadly digital trap, the members of the Justice League emerge in their own world to discover that Grimm, ravenous creatures from Remnant, have overtaken Earth! In order to defeat the monsters, they must call on their new friends – Team RWBY – for help!
cast: Troy Baker, Travis Willingham, Laura Bailey, Lindsay Jones, Kara Eberle

title: Iguana Like the Sun
description: In a humble coastal tropical compound, amidst a total eclipse of the sun, an unexpected guest arouses the broken dreams of a family that has lost its guardian figure, overshadowed by the cosmic loneliness where they were left to their faith.
cast: Dolores Heredia, Kristyan Ferrer, Luisa Huertas, Mayra Batalla, Fernando Álvarez Rebeil

title: The Six Million Dollar Man: Wine, Women and War
genres: Science Fiction, Action, Drama, TV Movie
description: After Col. Steve Austin fails to retrieve the contents of a safe owned by arms dealer Arlen Findletter, he accepts an offer of a holiday in the Bahamas. There he runs into Soviet Agent Alexi Kaslov and his lovely assistant Katrina Volana, who also happen to be out to find Findletter. Is it a coincidence, or was Steve's trip all part of one of Oscar Goldman's missions?
cast: Lee Majors, Richard Anderson, Alan Oppenheimer, Britt Ekland, Eric Braeden

title: Five Feet Apart
description: Seventeen-year-old Stella spends most of her time in the hospital as a cystic fibrosis patient. Her life is full of routines, boundaries and self-control — all of which get put to the test when she meets Will, an impossibly charming teen who has the same illness. There's an instant flirtation, though restrictions dictate that they must maintain a safe distance between them. As their connection intensifies, so does the temptation to throw the rules out the window and embrace that attraction.
cast: Haley Lu Richardson, Cole Sprouse, Moisés Arias, Kimberly Hébert Gregory, Parminder Nagra

title: Les Enfoirés 2011 - Dans l'oeil des Enfoirés
description: Dans l’œil des Enfoirés est le vingt-et-unième album des Enfoirés, enregistré lors de leurs sept concerts à l’Arena Montpellier du mercredi 26 janvier au lundi 31 janvier 2011.
cast: Pascal Obispo, Kad Merad, Gérard Jugnot, Mimie Mathy, Patrick Bruel

title: Liebe, Babys und ein großes Herz – Neue Wege
cast: Marion Kracht, Michael Roll, Julia Bremermann, Christiane Blumhoff, Markus Böker

title: Bad Boys for Life
description: Marcus and Mike are forced to confront new threats, career changes, and midlife crises as they join the newly created elite team AMMO of the Miami police department to take down the ruthless Armando Armas, the vicious leader of a Miami drug cartel.
cast: Will Smith, Martin Lawrence, Vanessa Hudgens, Alexander Ludwig, Charles Melton

title: Hitler: The Last Ten Days
description: Hitler: The Last Ten Days takes us into the depths of der Furher’s Berlin bunker during his final days. Based on the book by Gerhard Boldt, it provides a bleak look at the goings-on within, and without.
cast: Alec Guinness, Simon Ward, Adolfo Celi, Diane Cilento, Gabriele Ferzetti

title: Jon Lord with The Hoochie Coochie Men: Live at The Basement
description: Deep Purple's Jon Lord performs live at The Basement in Sydney in this exclusive concert alongside The Hoochie Coochie Men (Bob Daisley - bass, Tim Gaze - guitar and vocals, Rob Grosser - drums, Jim Conway - harmonica). Special Guest: Jimmy Barnes.
cast: Jon Lord, Bob Daisley, Rob Grosser, Tim Gaze, Jim Conway

title: Fight Another Day
description: Follows a tough cop, who after being transported to a dystopian future, must enter a deadly combat tournament to be able to return to his past.
cast: Jim Belushi, Martin Kove, Eric Johnson, Ennis Esmer, Chuck Liddell

title: Update Amore
description: All about loneliness, sensuality and poetry.

title: Götz von Berlichingen mit der eisernen Hand
